data.title: Performers
data.text:
The All-American Rejects

Since the start of their career, alt-rock/power pop titans The All-American Rejects have sold over 10 million albums worldwide and helped define a post-emo sound that was the soundtrack of a decade. With smash hits “Gives You Hell,” "Dirty Little Secret,” “Move Along,” “Swing, Swing,” and “It Ends Tonight,” their songs have become an indelible slice of the era. Frontman Tyson Ritter has also added acting to his creative arsenal most recently with credits including Love And Mercy, HBO’s Lewis & Clark, NBC’s Parenthood, and Betas.

Naval Air Station Joint Reserve Base New Orleans - May 16, 2024 | Construction Battalion Center Gulfport - May 17, 2024 | Naval Air Station Meridian - May 18, 2024

Andy Grammer

Emmy award winner and multi-platinum artist Andy Grammer engages, energizes, and empowers audiences with stomping stadium-size pop anthems meant to be shared at full volume. Andy Grammer has inspired fans worldwide, amassing over 3 billion streams globally. His discography features numerous hits such as the 4x Platinum "Honey, I’m Good," and Platinum singles "Keep Your Head Up," "Fine By Me," "Don’t Give Up On Me," "Fresh Eyes," and "Good To Be Alive (Hallelujah)," along with the Gold single "I Found You," and Gold albums Andy Grammer (2011) and Magazines Or Novels (2014). Grammer's releases also include popular tracks like "Lease On Life," "Damn It Feels Good To Be Me," "Love Myself," and "Good Man."

Naval Air Station Meridian - May 18, 2024 | Commander Fleet Activities Okinawa - May 21, 2024 | U.S. Naval Air Facility Atsugi - May 23, 2024 | Commander Fleet Activities Yokosuka - May 25, 2024 | U.S. Naval Joint Services Activity The New Sanno | May 27, 2024 | Commander Fleet Activities Sasebo - May 29, 2024

Brett Young

Brett Young's unique "Caliville" sound, a blend of California's laid-back style with Nashville's country essence, has led to seven #1 singles and over 8.1 billion streams. His music, marked by hits like the 9x Platinum "In Case You Didn’t Know," captures hearts with its emotional depth and storytelling. Brett Young's achievements, including the ACM New Male Artist award, and his recent album "Across The Sheets," highlight his impactful contribution to country music.

Naval Station Mayport - June 28, 2024

Cody Bradley

Cody Bradley is an up-and-coming artist, whose roots run deep in old-school country music. His style can be characterized as “a new boots” feel that is emphasized by his classic country mix. His diversity sets him apart, as he can effortlessly shift from soulful melodies to a rock-party anthem. His singles “L.A.” and “Kinda Hope We Don’t” show his ability to switch from “melodies to pull on your heartstrings” to “let’s rock this joint” from song to song. As an Army veteran, Bradley’s military background makes him rugged but relatable. Bradley’s goal is to pull people through the tough times and give them something to look forward to every day.

Naval Base Ventura County - May 19, 2024 | Naval Station Newport - June 21, 2024 | Naval Submarine Base New London - June 22, 2024

Colbie Caillat

Colbie Caillat is a 2x GRAMMY Award-winning, 5x GRAMMY Award-nominated singer/songwriter whose catalog has 15+ billion global streams. Her debut album COCO hit #5 on the Billboard Top 200 Albums chart and is certified 3x Platinum, while her Platinum-selling follow-up album Breakthrough landed at #1 on the Billboard album chart. Caillat’s radio career boasts eight #1 and/or top 10 singles including 6x Platinum-certified hit “Bubbly” and her GRAMMY-winning duet with Jason Mraz, “Lucky”. As an expert storyteller, her live show is personal and engaging from all the stages she plays, from arenas and festivals to intimate clubs.

Naval Station Norfolk - May 4, 2024 | Naval Support Facility Indian Head - May 17, 2024 | Naval Base Kitsap - June 1, 2024

Dierks Bentley

Dierks Bentley recently released his 10th studio album GRAVEL & GOLD, again “proving why he’s one of Country’s biggest stars” (TODAY) whose unique 21st-century career has had a rare consistency fueled by longevity. Throughout his two-decade career, Bentley has achieved success on the top of the Country sales charts, resulting in twenty-two #1 songs, 8 billion streams, 3 CMA Awards, 14 GRAMMY nominations, and membership into the Grand Ole Opry.

Naval Station Norfolk - May 4, 2024

Eli Young Band

Since the band’s formation as college classmates 20 years ago, the Associated Press has celebrated Eli Young Band as “a smart, relevant antidote” in Country music, while maintaining their Texas roots. The band has 14 Billboard singles, including 3x Platinum ‘Crazy Girl' and 2x Platinum 'Even If It Breaks Your Heart'. They've won an ACM Award for Song of the Year and received multiple GRAMMY and CMA nominations. While selling out venues from coast to coast as strong headliners, Eli Young Band has also shared the stage with Kenny Chesney, Rascal Flatts, Tim McGraw, Jason Aldean, Toby Keith, and Darius Rucker.

Naval Station Newport - June 21, 2024 | Naval Submarine Base New London - June 22, 2024

Everclear

Everclear, one of the leading alternative rock bands of the ‘90s, celebrated their 30th Anniversary in 2022. Since their formation in 1992, they have released 11 studio albums, with hits like 'Santa Monica', and four albums certified Gold or Platinum. Selling 6+ million records, Everclear's influence in alternative rock is undeniable. They continue to captivate fans worldwide with vibrant live performances, demonstrating a legacy of resilience, iconic music, and no signs of slowing down. This enduring appeal cements their significant place in the music industry.

Naval Support Activity Dahlgren - May 31, 2024

Goo Goo Dolls

Since forming in 1986, Goo Goo Dolls have set records and become staples in American music, connecting with millions over three decades. With 15 million records sold, four GRAMMY nominations, and numerous Gold and Platinum singles, they've marked history with hits like “Iris”, “Slide”, and “Better Days”, showcasing its timeless appeal with a recent resurgence on social media. Their influence spans across genres, as seen in covers by artists from Taylor Swift to Phoebe Bridgers and Maggie Rogers, continuing to win new fans and accolades globally.

Joint Base Pearl Harbor Hickham - May 17, 2024

Ivan Pecel

Based in Los Angeles, CA, Ivan Pecel elevates "high energy" to a new level with his unforgettable performances. Equally humorous as a stand-up comedian and as agile as a Chinese acrobat, Ivan has showcased his talents on MTV, 'America’s Got Talent,' and 'The Tonight Show with Jay Leno.' Whether he’s kicking a flaming torch over his head blindfolded, juggling ping pong balls with his mouth, or drawing laughter from the crowd, his dynamic shows captivate audiences of all sizes and in any venue.

Naval Support Activity Mechanicsburg - June 12, 2024

Jim Gaffigan

Jim Gaffigan is a seven-time GRAMMY-nominated comedian, actor, writer, producer, two-time New York Times best-selling author, three-time Emmy-winning top touring performer, and multi-Platinum-selling recording artist. He is known around the world for his unique brand of humor, which largely revolves around his observations on life. Gaffigan is a top ten comedian according to Forbes’ 2019 comedy list and top ten earning comedian in Pollstar’s 2022 list. He released his 10th comedy special, Dark Pale, an unprecedented achievement for the comedian/actor. Dark Pale was met with critical fanfare with The New York Times calling it, "his best yet."

Naval Station Great Lakes - May 8, 2024

Joel Meyers

Joel Meyers combines sleight of hand with his original routines, captivating audiences with his larger-than-life personality and charming presence. Described by NBC as a 'roller coaster ride,' Meyers excels as an illusionist, mentalist, and master magician. His performances, which Newsweek says 'will capture your imagination,' consistently delight and amaze. Meyers has appeared on 'America's Got Talent,' 'Masters of Illusion,' and 'Penn & Teller: Fool Us' on the CW. A man who believes the impossible is possible, Meyers infuses this belief into every captivating performance.

Naval Weapons Station Yorktown - June 12, 2024

Lauren Alaina

Grand Ole Opry member and Big Loud Records powerhouse, Lauren Alaina, is unlocking a new era. The multi-faceted star is stripping back every layer, allowing fans to know her more than ever before in her new EP, “Unlocked.” The star boasts hits like Platinum 'Road Less Traveled', 7x Platinum 'What Ifs' with Kane Brown, and 2x Platinum 'ONE BEER' with HARDY + Devin Dawson. Celebrated for her trajectory by American Songwriter, she's performed with icons such as Blake Shelton and Carrie Underwood. Winner of the 2018 ACM New Female Artist and 2017 CMT Breakthrough Video, her EP marks a personal evolution.

Naval Support Activity Dahlgren - May 31, 2024

Lecade

Cade Brinkley, better known as Lecade, is an independent country artist with hip-hop/rap influences, originally from Baton Rouge, Louisiana. He made his mark in the music industry from his home in Purvis, Mississippi, just south of Jackson. Lecade proudly represents his state, as evidenced in the song 'Mississippi' from his debut country album 'Chasing Ghosts'. His father, who played in several small-town country bands throughout the South, was his greatest musical inspiration from a young age.

Naval Air Station Kingsville - May 24, 2024 | Naval Air Station Corpus Christi - May 25, 2024

Little Big Town

Little Big Town, featuring Karen Fairchild, Phillip Sweet, Kimberly Schlapman, & Jimi Westbrook, first entered the music scene over 20 years ago. Their 10 studio albums, featuring hits like “Better Man,” “Little White Church,” “Day Drinking," and “Girl Crush”, have generated billions of streams. Little Big Town has earned more than 45 award show nominations and has taken home nearly 20 awards, including multiple GRAMMY, AMA, People’s Choice, CMA and ACM Awards, in addition to an Emmy award.

Naval Air Station Pensacola - May 18, 2024

lovelytheband

Formed in 2017 in Los Angeles, lovelytheband features Mitchy Collins, Jordan Greenwald, and Sam Price. Their debut single 'Broken' quickly climbed the Billboard Hot 100, marking their rapid rise. Known for catchy hooks and a blend of rock, pop, and indie, they've secured millions of streams and a strong fanbase. With singles like 'These Are My Friends' and albums 'Conversations with Myself About You' — spotlighting 'broken' atop Billboard Alternative Songs — and 'A Strange Arrangement,' their sound resonates widely. Their latest album, "if we’re being honest," released in 2023, continues their chart success and musical evolution.

Naval Support Activity Andersen - May 10, 2024 | Commander Fleet Activities Chinhae - May 12, 2024 | U.S. Naval Support Facility Diego Garcia - May 17 & 18, 2024 | Singapore Area Coordinator - May 24, 2024

Ludacris

Ludacris, born Christopher Brian Bridges in 1977, made a splash in 2000 and burst onto the scene in 2000 with "Back for the First Time.” His rapid-fire flow and witty wordplay made him a leading rapper with hits like 'Act a Fool' and 'My Chick Bad.” Albums 'Word of Mouf' and 'Chicken-n-Beer' are hip-hop staples. Earning 3 GRAMMYs and multiple Platinum records, Ludacris has been pivotal in shaping early 2000s hip-hop. His influence extends beyond music into acting, notably in the 'Fast & Furious' franchise, solidifying his status as a multifaceted entertainer.

Naval Air Station Patuxent River - May 23, 2024

Maddie & Tae

Award-winning duo Maddie & Tae, featuring longtime friends and collaborators Maddie Font and Taylor Kerr, are known for their honest songwriting, and “some of the tightest harmonies on Music Row” (Rolling Stone). They first broke out in 2013 with their brilliant counter to bro-country, the Platinum-selling smash, “Girl In A Country Song,” which took Country radio by storm, skyrocketing to the top of the charts. The pair continued to draw praise with their Gold-certified “The Way It Feels” album, including the 2x Platinum-certified No. 1 hit, “Die From A Broken Heart.” They have received numerous CMA, ACM, and CMT awards and nominations.

Naval Base Kitsap (Bremerton and Bangor) - June 1, 2024

Maren Morris

Maren Morris is one of today's leading voices in music, a powerhouse equipped with incredible vocal stylings, songwriting chops, sheer talent, and an undeniable presence. She has released three critically acclaimed albums—“HERO” in 2016, “GIRL” in 2019, and “Humble Quest” in 2022—and her 6x Platinum-certified hit collaboration, “The Middle,” with Zedd. In addition to a Grammy win and 17 nominations, Morris has garnered five ACM Awards, five CMA Awards, and three Billboard Music Awards, among other honors. She has broken streaming records, made multiple late-night TV appearances, guest-hosted 'Jimmy Kimmel Live!', and sold-out iconic venues worldwide during her tours.

Naval Air Station Pensacola - May 18, 2024

Michael Kent

Known as a Modern Day Magician, comedian and magician Michael Kent revitalizes magic with satirical and irreverent twists. Learning magic initially to make friends, he now performs globally, from Hollywood to US troops in 13 countries. His shows, reminiscent of a late-night talk show, blend sarcastic humor with impressive magic, inviting audiences to laugh at the absurdity and feel "in on the joke." Kent’s unique approach lets audiences experience the fusion of stand-up comedy with the art of magic, poking fun at its traditions.

Naval Support Activity Saratoga Springs - May 3, 2024

Plain White T's

Since 1997, the Chicago quartet Plain White T's have delivered unforgettable pop rock anthems, amassing 2.7+ billion streams and multiple Platinum and Gold certifications. 'Hey There Delilah' hit 4x Platinum, topped the Billboard Hot 100 and led to GRAMMY nominations in 2008. They have made their pop culture mark by appearing on highly visible shows such as the Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade, Sesame Street, and Beavis & Butthead, all the while nabbing press accolades from TIME, Billboard, ESPN, Rolling Stone, MTV, MSNBC, and more. Plain White T's have proven to be a reliable musical force, as well as a career band that shows no signs of stopping or slowing down.

Naval Support Activity Bahrain - May 15, 2024 | National Support Element, Isa - May 16, 2024 | Camp Lemonnier Djibouti - May 19, 2024 | Naval Station Everett - June 14, 2024 | Naval Air Station Whidbey Island - June 15, 2024

Rodney Atkins

Rodney Atkins is as authentic as they come. Whether he’s working on his land, spending time with his family, or entertaining thousands of fans with one of his many mega-hits, Atkins expresses a refreshing simplicity and sincerity that reflects the values he holds so dear: Putting family first, making the most of what you have, and staying true to yourself in a rapidly-­changing world. When he’s not in the studio working on new music, Atkins is working hard out on the road, connecting with loyal fans in cities across the country. An avid supporter of our military, with 14+ million records sold, 3.8+ billion on-demand streams, and multiple No.1s, Atkins has become the staple of country music.

Naval Station Rota - May 10, 2024 | Naval Support Activity Souda Bay - May 12, 2024 | Naval Support Activity Naples - May 13, 2024 | Naval Air Station Sigonella - May 17, 2024

Russell Dickerson

Russell Dickerson's third album marks a significant moment in his career, seamlessly blending heartfelt romance with country dynamism. Emerging from Nashville's vibrant music scene, his authentic storytelling has captivated millions, garnering billions of streams. Best known for hits like "Yours," “Blue Tacoma,” and “She Likes It,” Dickerson delves into themes of love, family, and friendship in his latest work, influenced by becoming a father and valuing connections. Bridging soulful melodies with pop and country, his music continues to resonate, showcasing his growth as an artist and individual.

Naval Base Ventura County - May 19, 2024

Ryan Hamilton

Ryan Hamilton recently released his first stand-up special. The one-hour Netflix original “Happy Face” follows a wealth of television appearances and a non-stop headlining tour. Armed with the unique perspective of growing up in rural Idaho to become a favorite in the New York stand-up comedy scene, he’s one-of-a-kind. He’s been named one of Rolling Stone’s Five Comics to Watch, and recent appearances include The Tonight Show with Jimmy Fallon, Late Show with Stephen Colbert, Conan, and opening spots for Jerry Seinfeld and Jim Gaffigan, as well as Gad Elmaleh at Carnegie Hall.

DATES COMING SOON!

Sasha McVeigh

Sasha McVeigh, with her unique blend of UK charm and Nashville sound, has emerged as a compelling British country music artist. Captivating audiences with her storytelling and powerful vocals, McVeigh has gained acclaim on both sides of the Atlantic. Her music journey, from intimate UK gigs to major US stages, highlights her global appeal. Infused with personal narratives and emotive melodies, her songs deeply resonate with fans. As she continues to release heartfelt singles and albums, McVeigh solidifies her place in country music, bridging cultures and connecting hearts.

Naval Support Activity Panama City - May 17, 2024

Scotty McCreery

Scotty McCreery launched his recording career by making history in 2011, being both the first country artist and the youngest male artist of any genre to debut his studio album, "Clear as Day," at No. 1 on the Billboard Top 200. Among his hits are “It Matters to Her,” “This Is It,” and “Damn Strait.” Notably, Rolling Stone recognized his work in their "40 Best Country and Americana Albums of 2018." With five studio albums, four have debuted at No. 1 on Billboard, contributing to five consecutive No.1 hits, earning him a Double Platinum, 4x Platinum, and 4x Gold singles, along with one Platinum and two Gold albums. McCreery's song “Five More Minutes” inspired a Hallmark movie, showcasing his impact beyond music..

Naval Air Station Kingsville - May 24, 2024 | Naval Air Station Corpus Christi - May 25, 2024

Thompson Square

Thompson Square is an acclaimed country music duo composed of husband and wife, Keifer and Shawna Thompson. Since breaking onto the scene in 2010, they have carved out a unique niche with their harmonious blend of vocals and heartfelt songwriting. Their breakthrough hit, "Are You Gonna Kiss Me Or Not," became a chart-topping success and earned them several awards, including two Academy of Country Music Awards. Known for their dynamic live performances, Thompson Square continues to connect deeply with fans around the world. With three albums under their belt and a reputation for authentic, emotionally resonant music, they remain a beloved staple in the country music community.

Naval Ordnance Test Unit Cape Canaveral - June 22, 2024

White Panda

White Panda has made a name as a standout mashup act, merging genres to dominate SoundCloud charts. Known for electrifying mixes and remixes, White Panada combines hip-hop with electronic dance music, crafting a sound that has captivated a global audience. Live performances are a visual and auditory feast, marked by vibrant visuals and pulsating beats. With albums like “Night Club,” “Bearly Legal,” “Bambooyah!,” and a series of viral hits, White Panda has carved out a pioneering space in the mashup genre, always exploring new musical territories.

DATES COMING SOON!
